<h2 id="原文摘要">原文摘要
</h2><p>Gitanjali Rao, a rising junior at MIT majoring in biological engineering, has been named the first-ever recipient of the Stephen Hawking Junior Medal for Science Communication. This award, presented by the Starmus Festival, is a new category of the already prestigious award created by the late theoretical physicist, cosmologist, and author Stephen Hawking and the Starmus Festival.</p>
<p>“I spend a lot of time in labs,” says Rao, highlighting her Undergraduate Research Opportunities Program project in&hellip;</p>
